# Testing - Node.js / React / Vitest / Playwright

## Guiding Principles

1. **Test-Driven Development (TDD)**
   - Write failing tests first, then implement the minimum code to pass, and finally refactor.
   - Each red-green-refactor loop should be < 10 min to keep feedback fast.

2. **Test Pyramid**
End-to-end (Playwright) - few, broad, slow
Integration (Vitest + real adapters) - moderate
Unit (Vitest + mocks) - many, fast, focused

## Best Practices

| Level | Focus | Guidelines |
|-------|-------|------------|
| **Unit** | Pure functions, domain logic, React components in isolation | • Keep test boundaries tight — mock external collaborators (DB, network, timers).<br>• Apply **DRY** setup helpers (see *Setup Patterns*). |
| **Integration** | Multiple modules wired together (e.g. service + repo hitting an in-memory DB) | • Spin up real adapters where feasible.<br>• Avoid third-party mocks; prefer lightweight test doubles (SQLite, DynamoLocal, MSW). |
| **End-to-End** | Critical user flows across the full stack | • Write Playwright tests for happy paths **and** edge cases.<br>• Keep E2E suite small & critical—smoke the most important journeys.<br>• Parallelise in CI and reuse browsers for speed. |

### Edge-Case Coverage
Test edge case scenarios, e.g.:

- Invalid or missing inputs
- Large payloads / pagination limits
- Boundary dates & numbers (epoch, max int, leap year)
- Concurrent updates / race conditions
- Permission or feature-flag toggles

### Patterns & Techniques

- **Given-When-Then** structure in every test.
- **Queries over Assertions** - assert on rendered output or public API, never on internals.
- **Snapshot tests** sparingly; prefer explicit assertions.
- **Deterministic timing** - fake timers for time-dependent logic.
- **Seed data once** per test file via `beforeAll`; reset state in `beforeEach`.
- **Parallel safe** - tests must not rely on execution order or global shared state.

### Quality Gates

- **Coverage targets**: 90%+ for domain logic, 80% overall.
